Apertural lip thickness varies greatly, protecting the snail's soft body inside.
They often inhabit shallow pools and lily pad patches during the warmer seasons.
Muddy riverbanks and submerged roots provide stable resting surfaces for adults.
Whispering marsh grasses and reeds form critical nursery areas for the young beetles.
