The slippery slope fallacy suggests a minor action leads to catastrophe. We must examine the actual causal links instead of accepting the exaggerated, worst-case scenario.
Because the dog only barks at the mailman, he likely knows the pattern. If he were scared, he would bark at everything. Therefore, his behavior suggests familiarity, not fear.
Because the recipe calls for fresh basil, the flavor will be vibrant. If you use dried herbs, the taste will be dull. Therefore, quality ingredients matter greatly for good cooking.
