Punctuality standards differ globally. While some cultures consider being late merely inconvenient, others perceive it as a profound sign of disrespect and poor planning.
For language learners, a global review of proverbs and idioms is crucial; meaning often changes dramatically when moving across cultural boundaries.
When giving feedback across cultures, structure it gently and indirectly, especially in high-context societies. Direct criticism can be perceived as offensive, so tact is paramount.
When discussing tipping etiquette, remember that service gratuities vary dramatically across cultures; a final review of local customs is essential for respectful travel.
